      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> with the <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and <strong>sesame oil </strong>and bring to the boil</p>",
